ANNEX   I 
 
Schedule of Brunei Darussalam 
 
Headnote 
 
Elimination of Customs Duties on Goods Originating 
in Chile, New Zealand or Singapore  
 
 
 
Introductory notes 
 
I.  The tariff schedule in this Annex contains the following four columns: 
 
(a)  “Code”: the code used in the nomenclature of the ASEAN Harmonised Tariff 
Nomenclature  (AHTN) 2004. 
 
(b)  “Description”: the description of the product falling under the heading. 
 
(c)  “Base  Rate”:  the  basic  customs  duty  from  which  the  tariff  elimination 
programme starts. 
 
(d)  “End date”: the year in which the tariff goes to zero (i.e. tariff free) for the 
product concerned. 
 
 
II.  Except as otherwise provided in this Agreement, Brunei Darussalam shall 
progressively  eliminate  its  customs  duties  on  originating  goods  of  Chile, 
New Zealand and Singapore in accordance with its Tariff Schedule in this Annex.  
The base rate and the interim rate of customs duty at each stage of reduction for an 
item are indicated for the item in the Schedule.  Reductions shall occur on 1 January 
of each year, as provided for in the Schedule.   
 
I-BN-1 Annex I: Brunei Darusslam's Tariff Schedule
